  "solution": [
    "## Solutions to Quadratic Curves Recognition Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: Discriminant Analysis",
    "",
    "**a)** Δ = 0 - 4(4)(9) = -144 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**b)** Δ = 4 - 4(1)(1) = 0 → parabola",
    "",
    "**c)** Δ = 1 - 4(3)(3) = 1 - 36 = -35 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**d)** Δ = 16 - 4(2)(3) = 16 - 24 = -8 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**e)** Δ = 4 - 4(5)(5) = 4 - 100 = -96 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: Invariant Method",
    "",
    "**a)** I = 2+3 = 5, II = 6 - 1/4 = 23/4 > 0, Δ = 1-24 = -23 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**b)** I = 1-2 = -1, II = -2 - 9/4 = -2 - 2.25 = -4.25 < 0, Δ = 9-4(1)(-2) = 9+8 = 17 > 0 → hyperbola",
    "",
    "**c)** I = 4+1 = 5, II = 4 - 1 = 3 > 0, III = det of full matrix, Δ = 4 - 16 = -12 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**d)** I = 3+2 = 5, II = 6 - 1/4 = 23/4 > 0, Δ = 1-24 = -23 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**e)** I = 6+4 = 10, II = 24 - 1 = 23 > 0, Δ = 4 - 96 = -92 < 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Matrix Method",
    "",
    "**a)** A = [[1,2],[2,4]], det(A) = 4-8 = -4 < 0, trace = 5 > 0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**b)** A = [[2,0.5],[0.5,2]], eigenvalues λ = (4 ± √(16-4))/2 = (4 ± √12)/2 = 2 ± √3",
    "",
    "**c)** det(A) = 3*1 - 1 = 2 > 0, but need full classification",
    "",
    "**d)** A = [[5,2],[2,3]], det = 15-4 = 11 > 0, both eigenvalues positive → ellipse",
    "",
    "**e)** Sylvester: principal minors 4>0, det(A)=4*2-1=7>0 → ellipse",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Completing the Square",
    "",
    "**a)** 9(x² - 4x + 4) + 4(y² + 2y + 1) = 4 + 36 + 4 = 44, 9(x-2)² + 4(y+1)² = 44 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**b)** (x+1)² + (y-2)² = 4 → circle (special ellipse)",
    "",
    "**c)** 4(x+2)² + 9(y-1)² = 36 + 144 + 81 + 11 = 272 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**d)** 2(x+1)² + 2(y-2)² = 3 + 2 + 8 = 13 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**e)** 3(x-1)² + 3(y+2)² = 9 + 12 + 9 = 30 → circle",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: Rotation of Axes",
    "",
    "**a)** tan(2θ) = -4/(2-5) = -4/(-3) = 4/3, θ = (1/2)arctan(4/3)",
    "",
    "**b)** tan(2θ) = √3/(1-1) undefined, θ = π/4",
    "",
    "**c)** tan(2θ) = 1/(3-3) undefined, θ = π/4, then classify",
    "",
    "**d)** tan(2θ) = 4/(5-8) = 4/(-3) = -4/3",
    "",
    "**e)** After rotation, check coefficients of x'², y'² terms",
    "",
    "### Exercise 6: Degenerate Cases",
    "",
    "**a)** (x-1)² + (y-1)² = 0 → single point",
    "",
    "**b)** 2(x-0.5)² + 2(y-0.5)² = 0 → single point",
    "",
    "**c)** (3x-y+3)² = 0 → single line",
    "",
    "**d)** (x+y+1)² = 0 → single line",
    "",
    "**e)** When III = 0, check if it's two lines, point, or single line",
    "",
    "### Exercise 7: Center and Symmetry",
    "",
    "**a)** ∂f/∂x = 4x + 4 = 0 → x = -1, ∂f/∂y = 6y - 6 = 0 → y = 1, center (-1,1)",
    "",
    "**b)** Center (2, -1), symmetric ellipse",
    "",
    "**c)** Center (-1, 2), circle",
    "",
    "**d)** Center (-1, -1), ellipse",
    "",
    "**e)** Ellipse/hyperbola have centers, parabola has vertex",
    "",
    "### Exercise 8: Focus and Directrix",
    "",
    "**a)** Focus (2,0), directrix x = -2, e = 1",
    "",
    "**b)** c = √(9-4) = √5, foci (0, ±√5), directrix y = ±9/√5, e = √5/3",
    "",
    "**c)** c = √(16+9) = 5, foci (±5,0), directrix x = ±16/5, e = 5/4",
    "",
    "**d)** e = c/a from standard form",
    "",
    "**e)** e < 1 ellipse, e = 1 parabola, e > 1 hyperbola",
    "",
    "### Exercise 9: Parametric Classification",
    "",
    "**a)** x²/4 + y²/9 = 1 → ellipse",
    "",
    "**b)** x²/9 - y²/4 = 1 → hyperbola",
    "",
    "**c)** x = t², y = 2t → y² = 4x → parabola",
    "",
    "**d)** x²/4 - y²/9 = 1 → hyperbola",
    "",
    "**e)** Check if parameters satisfy conic definitions",
    "",
    "### Exercise 10: Intersection Classification",
    "",
    "**a)** Two intersection points → ellipse/hyperbola",
    "",
    "**b)** Tangent (one intersection point) → parabola",
    "",
    "**c)** No intersection → imaginary conic",
    "",
    "**d)** Two points: ellipse/hyperbola, one point: parabola, none: imaginary",
    "",
    "**e)** Multiplicity indicates tangency",
    "",
    "### Exercise 11: Asymptotic Behavior",
    "",
    "**a)** y = ±(3/2)x",
    "",
    "**b)** Slope of asymptotes = √(b²/a²) = b/a",
    "",
    "**c)** Straight asymptotes → hyperbola",
    "",
    "**d)** Asymptotes define hyperbola orientation",
    "",
    "**e)** Rectangular hyperbola if asymptotes perpendicular",
    "",
